## File Structure
```
src/app/api/<resource>/route.ts         → API routes
src/app/<page>/page.tsx                 → Pages (Server Components by default)
src/components/ui/                      → shadcn/ui (DO NOT MODIFY)
src/components/<domain>/               → Domain components
src/lib/db.ts                          → Prisma client
src/lib/logger.ts                      → Pino logger
src/lib/api-utils.ts                   → withApiContext, logActivity
src/lib/services/                      → Business logic
src/lib/utils/                         → Pure utilities
prisma/schema.prisma                   → DB schema (90 models)
```

---

## Component Rules
- Default to Server Components in `app/`
- Add `'use client'` only for: event handlers, hooks, browser APIs
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classnames
- Use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/`

---

## Soft Delete Pattern
Most entities support soft delete. Always:
```typescript
// Query
prisma.entity.findMany({ where: { deletedAt: null } })

// Delete (use soft delete service, not prisma.delete)
import { softDeleteService } from '@/lib/services/governance'
```

---

## Avoid
- `console.log` / `console.error` / `console.warn`
- `any` type
- Unvalidated API inputs
- Modifying `src/components/ui/` files
- Using raw `prisma.entity.delete()` on soft-deletable models
- Hardcoding config values that belong in `.env`
- Unnecessary comments on self-explanatory code
- Over-engineering: keep it simple, no premature abstractions
